A vintage-style illustration of a Japanese zen garden with carefully arranged stones, where each stone has a small colorful paper tag tied to it with string, fluttering gently in the breeze. In the center, a wise owl wearing round spectacles perches on a weathered wooden post, surveying the tagged stones with serene attention. The scene is bathed in warm sepia and amber tones with soft vignetting around the edges, evoking early 20th century botanical illustrations. Delicate brushwork shows cherry blossom petals drifting through the air, some landing on the tagged stones. The composition suggests a peaceful system of organization and mindful curation, with each tag representing a bookmark waiting to be discovered.
